Bisola Aiyeola, runner up of BBNaija season two ‘See Gobe’ on Thursday paid housemates a surprise visit Bisola encouraged the ‘Pepper Dem Housemates’ to stay focused as the season draws to a close. She was accompanied by singer, Aituaje Iruobe aka Waje and Sarah Amaka, country director for ONE, Nigeria. After a rousing welcome from the five ‘Pepper Dem’ finalists, Bisola shared her experience while in the house, adding that she could relate to the feelings of the housemates. She said, “I know how you feel because I have been there. The hours will drag and you can’t just wait to be done. You guys have had a good run. Well done.” The Pepper Dem Gang was tasked with creating awareness for standard health care in Nigeria. Also, Waje encouraged the housemates to put in their best and focus on the task at hand, urging them to provide practical solutions to the tasks. Only five housemates – Mercy, Mike, Frodd, Seyi and Omashola are competing for the Grand prize worth N60 million. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.